[To find Laprida, go to http://www.fallingrain.com/world/AR/01/Laprida.html

Having multiple outbreaks on estancias without prior history, in the same area, and in these rapid numbers makes one suspect that we are seeing a series of outbreaks thanks to tabanid biting-fly activity. As we have seen in Italy, Canada (Manitoba and Saskatchewan), and the USA (SE Texas) these can get really nasty. The best response is area-wide vaccination; even revaccination if the owners claim that their stock were vaccinated in the Spring. While such epidemics usually involve just a single strain, investigations in Italy by Antonio Fasanella have shown that a minor strain or 2 can jump on the fly train and initiate subsidiary cases, even outbreaks. - Mod.MHJ

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/5KK9.]
